@rasbt @kohjingyu No. 
Classic Siamese net, SimCLR etc are *sample contrastive*: they push representation vectors from different samples far apart.
Barlow Twins &amp; its successor VICReg, are *dimension contrastive*: they push individual variables of the representation to be different from each other

